title: Led Zeppelin 1975.03.21 - Seattle
description:
I&#039;m not feeling well this week - it&#039;s time for my spring ritual of antibiotics and inhalers and just trying to breathe.

Seattle 1975.03.21 - one of Zeppelin&#039;s best shows ever.  I do like the recording, also - a fine job of digitizing the 1st-gen reels to DVD-Audio by Presence, it left me nothing to do but downsample to Audio CD and track up.  

This show really is everything you&#039;ve ever heard it was.  One thing I do feel like staying awake to note is that everyone should re-engineer a show at least once - you end up listening between songs a lot and you hear things that you might not have heard otherwise - an example of this is a female fan who cries out in recognition of a new track off "Physical Graffiti" at the first note - like she had been waiting forever to hear "In My Time Of Dying."  

Share and enjoy.  Seed.
TimD
